The paper discusses the use of deep neural networks for playing the game of Othello, which involves decision-making and strategy. This suggests that it could fall under the categories of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), Machine Learning (cs.LG), Computer Vision (cs.CV), Game Theory (cs.GT), and Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE). Among these, cs.AI and cs.LG are the most likely categories as they deal with the use of AI and machine learning techniques for decision-making tasks. The use of convolutional neural networks also suggests a possible fit under cs.CV. The paper also discusses the game theory aspects of Othello, which could place it under cs.GT. Finally, the use of neural networks for training and prediction could also make it relevant to cs.NE.
